WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.162 --> 00:00:09.162
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

2
00:00:11.366 --> 00:00:12.906
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(WATER RUNNING)</font>

3
00:00:28.550 --> 00:00:30.590
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(SPEAKING GERMAN)</font>

4
00:01:12.161 --> 00:01:14.721
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(WOMAN SPEAKING GERMAN
OVER PA)</font>

5
00:01:29.678 --> 00:01:30.948
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(HISSING)</font>

6
00:02:04.813 --> 00:02:06.073
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Scissors.</font>

7
00:02:10.519 --> 00:02:11.689
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Clamp.</font>

8
00:02:15.224 --> 00:02:16.594
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(PHONE BEEPING)</font>

9
00:02:17.759 --> 00:02:20.129
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">O.R.
Dr. Rogers for Dr. Carson.</font>

10
00:02:20.161 --> 00:02:21.461
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Doctor?</font>

11
00:02:23.164 --> 00:02:24.734
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes?
Ben, it's Mark.</font>

12
00:02:24.766 --> 00:02:26.066
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I need to see you
up in my office.</font>

13
00:02:26.100 --> 00:02:28.340
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">A special-needs case
just came in.</font>

14
00:02:28.370 --> 00:02:29.940
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Okay. Soon as I'm done.</font>

15
00:02:32.173 --> 00:02:34.243
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">They were born by cesarean
three months ago,</font>

16
00:02:34.276 --> 00:02:37.016
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and, against all odds,
they're still alive.</font>

17
00:02:40.148 --> 00:02:44.158
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Their physician
from West Germany
called me this morning.</font>

18
00:02:44.185 --> 00:02:49.185
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Occipital craniopagus twins
have never both
survived a separation.</font>

19
00:02:49.224 --> 00:02:50.954
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yeah. He knows that.</font>

20
00:02:55.364 --> 00:02:56.794
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If they're not separated...</font>

21
00:03:00.602 --> 00:03:05.972
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">...they'll spend
the rest of their lives
in bed, on their backs.</font>

22
00:03:06.007 --> 00:03:09.417
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The hospital wants me
to fly to Germany
and examine them.</font>

23
00:03:13.748 --> 00:03:15.948
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Ben, are you gonna do this?</font>

24
00:03:15.984 --> 00:03:17.584
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Nobody's ever done it.</font>

25
00:03:19.087 --> 00:03:23.157
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">In situations like this,
one baby always dies.</font>

26
00:03:28.897 --> 00:03:30.467
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN: Welcome to Germany.</font>

27
00:03:30.499 --> 00:03:32.669
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We've been anxiously
awaiting your arrival,
Dr. Carson.</font>

28
00:03:34.235 --> 00:03:37.405
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Allow me to introduce
Peter and Augusta Rausch.</font>

29
00:03:37.439 --> 00:03:38.809
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(INDISTINCT)</font>

30
00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:40.350
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thank you
for coming.</font>

31
00:03:40.375 --> 00:03:41.975
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">How do you do, Doctor?
My pleasure.</font>

32
00:03:42.010 --> 00:03:44.520
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And this is
Johann and Stefan.</font>

33
00:04:19.848 --> 00:04:23.488
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I wanted to kill myself
when I learned the truth,</font>

34
00:04:23.518 --> 00:04:27.028
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but I realized
I would be killing
two other beings, too.</font>

35
00:04:29.223 --> 00:04:32.793
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And then,
as soon as I saw them,
my heart melted.</font>

36
00:04:32.827 --> 00:04:36.467
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Please don't ask us
to choose between them.</font>

37
00:04:40.134 --> 00:04:45.404
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Well, they don't appear
to be sharing any organs,
which is good.</font>

38
00:04:45.440 --> 00:04:48.610
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Though there are
parts of the brain,
such as the vision center,</font>

39
00:04:48.643 --> 00:04:51.513
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">that aren't
completely separated.</font>

40
00:04:51.546 --> 00:04:53.346
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We won't know
until we get in there.</font>

41
00:04:53.382 --> 00:04:55.242
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">How soon can that be?</font>

42
00:04:55.283 --> 00:04:59.923
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Well, first we have to
solve the problem
of exsanguination.</font>

43
00:04:59.954 --> 00:05:01.324
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Exsan...</font>

44
00:05:01.356 --> 00:05:03.756
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Bleeding to death.</font>

45
00:05:03.792 --> 00:05:07.222
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's the reason why
cranial separations
have never succeeded.</font>

46
00:05:09.230 --> 00:05:13.870
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You see,
babies have
very little blood,</font>

47
00:05:13.902 --> 00:05:17.902
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and unless I can
figure out a way to
keep them from bleeding out,</font>

48
00:05:20.809 --> 00:05:23.449
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I can't risk performing
this operation.</font>

49
00:05:26.047 --> 00:05:27.687
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(INHALES SHARPLY)</font>

50
00:06:30.879 --> 00:06:32.049
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'll do it.</font>

51
00:06:35.517 --> 00:06:37.087
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Good.</font>

52
00:06:37.118 --> 00:06:39.588
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thank you.
I'll notify the doctor
in Germany.</font>

53
00:06:39.621 --> 00:06:42.891
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We'll schedule
the operation
for a month from now?</font>

54
00:06:42.924 --> 00:06:44.924
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Make it two. Make it four.</font>

55
00:06:47.295 --> 00:06:49.325
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Still haven't figured out
how to save them both, huh?</font>

56
00:06:49.363 --> 00:06:50.433
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(SIGHING)</font>

57
00:06:50.465 --> 00:06:51.465
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm working on it.</font>

58
00:07:09.150 --> 00:07:15.360
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Number 12, 14.
Number 13, 27.</font>

59
00:07:16.591 --> 00:07:19.891
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Number 15, 33.</font>

60
00:07:19.928 --> 00:07:22.898
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">All right, class,
hand your test back
to your neighbor.</font>

61
00:07:28.369 --> 00:07:30.739
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">All right, how many
did you get right?</font>

62
00:07:30.772 --> 00:07:31.832
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Kathy?</font>

63
00:07:31.873 --> 00:07:32.903
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Twenty-five.</font>

64
00:07:32.941 --> 00:07:35.101
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That's excellent, Kathy.</font>

65
00:07:35.910 --> 00:07:37.780
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mark?
Thirty.</font>

66
00:07:37.812 --> 00:07:39.982
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Good for you, Mark.
You got them all right.</font>

67
00:07:40.682 --> 00:07:41.842
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Benjamin?</font>

68
00:07:44.553 --> 00:07:47.523
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Benjamin, how many
did you get right?</font>

69
00:07:47.556 --> 00:07:49.626
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">None.
Nine?</font>

70
00:07:49.658 --> 00:07:52.628
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Why, Benjamin,
that's wonderful.
I'm so proud of you.</font>

71
00:07:52.661 --> 00:07:56.391
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Not nine, Miss Williamson.
He got none.</font>

72
00:07:56.430 --> 00:07:58.170
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CHILDREN LAUGHING)</font>

73
00:08:03.337 --> 00:08:04.707
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)</font>

74
00:08:10.144 --> 00:08:12.814
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You'd think he'd get
at least one right.</font>

75
00:08:12.847 --> 00:08:16.887
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">He got one right last time,
'cause he was trying
to put down the wrong answer.</font>

76
00:08:16.918 --> 00:08:18.418
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CHILDREN LAUGHING)</font>

77
00:08:18.452 --> 00:08:21.352
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Hey, Carson, we know
you're the dumbest kid
in the class,</font>

78
00:08:21.389 --> 00:08:23.929
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but did you hear
what they said on Cronkite
last night on the news?</font>

79
00:08:23.958 --> 00:08:26.058
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You're the dumbest kid
in the world.</font>

80
00:08:28.062 --> 00:08:29.222
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CHILDREN GASPING)</font>

81
00:08:29.263 --> 00:08:31.133
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">He hit him!
He hit him!</font>

82
00:08:31.165 --> 00:08:33.105
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">PRINCIPAL:
Bennie, how could this
have been an accident?</font>

83
00:08:33.134 --> 00:08:36.534
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Well, it was almost
an accident.</font>

84
00:08:36.571 --> 00:08:41.671
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mom, I never would have
hit him if I remembered
I had the lock in my hand.</font>

85
00:08:41.710 --> 00:08:46.050
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The boy had five stitches,
and his parents
are very upset.</font>

86
00:08:46.080 --> 00:08:48.250
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm not sure how to
discipline your son,
Mrs. Carson.</font>

87
00:08:48.282 --> 00:08:49.852
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'll handle it.</font>

88
00:08:49.884 --> 00:08:51.854
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm also very concerned
about his grades.</font>

89
00:08:51.886 --> 00:08:53.956
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Have you seen
his latest report card?</font>

90
00:09:00.461 --> 00:09:03.561
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">SONYA: So, what happened?
You weren't getting grades
like that in Boston.</font>

91
00:09:03.598 --> 00:09:06.168
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Boston was easier.
They didn't ask us
to do much.</font>

92
00:09:06.200 --> 00:09:08.640
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Well, I ain't
asking you, either,
I'm telling you.</font>

93
00:09:08.670 --> 00:09:11.080
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You weren't meant
to be a failure, Bennie.</font>

94
00:09:11.105 --> 00:09:12.805
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And you can
control your temper.
He called me a dummy...</font>

95
00:09:12.841 --> 00:09:15.001
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And you can
bring your grades up, too.
I know you can.</font>

96
00:09:15.043 --> 00:09:16.943
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm dumb, Mother.
No, you ain't.</font>

97
00:09:16.978 --> 00:09:21.048
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You're a smart boy.
Listen to me.
Listen to me.</font>

98
00:09:21.082 --> 00:09:24.452
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You just ain't
using that smartness.</font>

99
00:09:24.485 --> 00:09:26.585
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Now, if you keep
getting grades like that,</font>

100
00:09:26.621 --> 00:09:28.381
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">you're gonna
spend the rest of your life
mopping floors in a factory.</font>

101
00:09:28.422 --> 00:09:30.952
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And that ain't
the life I want for you.</font>

102
00:09:30.992 --> 00:09:33.462
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That ain't the life
God wants for you,
either.</font>

103
00:09:34.195 --> 00:09:36.895
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes, Mother.</font>

104
00:09:36.931 --> 00:09:40.531
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm gonna have to have
a talk with him about you
and your brother, Curtis.</font>

105
00:09:42.403 --> 00:09:45.803
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No, no. He invited us
to the game tonight,
remember?</font>

106
00:09:45.840 --> 00:09:49.680
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Why don't you and I go?
And get me
Candlestick Park, please.</font>

107
00:09:49.711 --> 00:09:50.811
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(DOOR OPENING)</font>

108
00:09:51.813 --> 00:09:55.583
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Hey, Mother.
You're home early.</font>

109
00:09:55.616 --> 00:09:58.686
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">They didn't need me
as long as they said
they would.</font>

110
00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:00.360
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You finish
your homework?</font>

111
00:10:01.656 --> 00:10:03.796
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Most of it.</font>

112
00:10:03.825 --> 00:10:07.325
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">SONYA: Bennie, you're gonna
ruin your eyes
sitting so close to this TV.</font>

113
00:10:07.361 --> 00:10:08.661
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(TURNS OFF TV)</font>

114
00:10:08.697 --> 00:10:09.767
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You do your homework?</font>

115
00:10:09.798 --> 00:10:11.068
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN: I need help.</font>

116
00:10:11.099 --> 00:10:12.399
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Curtis, help your brother.</font>

117
00:10:12.433 --> 00:10:14.033
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CURTIS:
I gotta finish my math.</font>

118
00:10:17.939 --> 00:10:20.409
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mother, I need help.</font>

119
00:10:20.441 --> 00:10:22.041
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What you need help with?</font>

120
00:10:22.076 --> 00:10:25.516
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">This history.
I don't really
understand it.</font>

121
00:10:25.546 --> 00:10:27.886
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Well, what don't
you understand?</font>

122
00:10:27.916 --> 00:10:30.916
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Like, all the words.</font>

123
00:10:30.952 --> 00:10:32.582
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Could you
read this for me?</font>

124
00:10:35.456 --> 00:10:39.456
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I need new reading glasses.
Why don't you tell me
what it's about?</font>

125
00:10:39.493 --> 00:10:42.063
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's about Thomas Jefferson
and the Declaration
of Independence.</font>

126
00:10:42.096 --> 00:10:43.736
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mmm-hmm.</font>

127
00:10:43.765 --> 00:10:45.935
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What is this word?</font>

128
00:10:45.967 --> 00:10:47.107
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Sound it out.</font>

129
00:10:50.739 --> 00:10:54.149
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"Self... Self...</font>

130
00:10:55.043 --> 00:10:58.473
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"And it..."</font>

131
00:10:59.914 --> 00:11:00.984
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Self...</font>

132
00:11:01.015 --> 00:11:02.145
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Look at me.</font>

133
00:11:04.986 --> 00:11:08.056
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Can you tell me
what them cereal boxes
is on the shelf?</font>

134
00:11:10.124 --> 00:11:11.854
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Sure.</font>

135
00:11:11.893 --> 00:11:14.093
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I mean, can you read them?</font>

136
00:11:14.128 --> 00:11:16.328
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Not this far. Can you?</font>

137
00:11:17.832 --> 00:11:18.932
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(SIGHING)</font>

138
00:11:27.208 --> 00:11:31.048
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Looks like I ain't
the only one around here
gonna be needing glasses.</font>

139
00:11:33.481 --> 00:11:41.381
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Tina, Sarah, Kathy, Bennie.</font>

140
00:11:41.422 --> 00:11:44.822
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Congratulations.
You're doing much better.</font>

141
00:11:47.495 --> 00:11:48.765
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes!</font>

142
00:11:50.664 --> 00:11:53.934
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">SONYA:
Well, it's an improvement,
all right.</font>

143
00:11:53.968 --> 00:11:56.608
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And I'm proud of you
for not getting an F.</font>

144
00:11:56.637 --> 00:11:59.177
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You're a smart boy.</font>

145
00:11:59.207 --> 00:12:00.647
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But you both
can do better.</font>

146
00:12:00.674 --> 00:12:01.774
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm doing the best
I can, Mother.</font>

147
00:12:01.810 --> 00:12:02.880
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">How?
I don't know how.</font>

148
00:12:02.911 --> 00:12:04.211
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Well, I don't know how.</font>

149
00:12:04.245 --> 00:12:05.975
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We're just gonna
have to
use our imagination.</font>

150
00:12:06.014 --> 00:12:07.814
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't got one.</font>

151
00:12:07.849 --> 00:12:11.419
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Of course you do.
Everybody got
an imagination.</font>

152
00:12:11.452 --> 00:12:12.552
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Not me.</font>

153
00:12:12.586 --> 00:12:13.956
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Of course you do.</font>

154
00:12:13.988 --> 00:12:17.728
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Listen to me.
If I say,</font>

155
00:12:17.758 --> 00:12:20.628
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">"Once upon a time,
there was
a little blue mouse,"</font>

156
00:12:20.661 --> 00:12:23.091
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">don't you see
a little blue mouse?</font>

157
00:12:23.131 --> 00:12:24.931
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No.
Bennie.</font>

158
00:12:24.966 --> 00:12:26.566
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mother, my brain's too dumb.</font>

159
00:12:26.600 --> 00:12:28.370
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Boy, your brain ain't dumb.</font>

160
00:12:28.402 --> 00:12:30.732
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It is, Mom.</font>

161
00:12:30.771 --> 00:12:33.571
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You got all the world
in here.</font>

162
00:12:35.243 --> 00:12:38.473
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You just got to see beyond
what you can see.</font>

163
00:12:45.086 --> 00:12:46.986
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN ON TV: What is this,
a race of some kind?</font>

164
00:12:47.021 --> 00:12:48.821
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">WOMAN ON TV:
Betty, slow down.</font>

165
00:12:48.857 --> 00:12:50.457
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You act as though
this were
your last meal.</font>

166
00:12:50.491 --> 00:12:53.321
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We've got to write
your contest essay
tonight, Father.</font>

167
00:12:53.361 --> 00:12:56.261
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN ON TV:
Oh, well, in that case,
maybe you had better hurry.</font>

168
00:12:56.297 --> 00:12:57.637
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(PHONE RINGS ON TV)</font>

169
00:12:57.665 --> 00:12:58.935
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN ON TV: Don't choke.
WOMAN ON TV: I'll get it.</font>

170
00:12:58.967 --> 00:13:00.807
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I never saw it
to fail.</font>

171
00:13:00.835 --> 00:13:03.275
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Every time
we sit down to eat,
the phone rings.</font>

172
00:13:03.304 --> 00:13:04.934
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">GIRL ON TV: I know
how to stop it, Daddy.</font>

173
00:13:04.973 --> 00:13:08.373
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">When the phone bill comes,
don't pay it.</font>

174
00:13:08.409 --> 00:13:09.809
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN ON TV:
Not a bad idea.</font>

175
00:13:09.844 --> 00:13:11.914
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BOY ON TV:
That was Joe Phillips, Dad.</font>

176
00:13:11.946 --> 00:13:13.086
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">He wants me to
come up to his uncle's farm
this weekend.</font>

177
00:13:13.114 --> 00:13:14.144
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Isn't that great?</font>

178
00:13:14.182 --> 00:13:15.912
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But how are you
gonna get there?</font>

179
00:13:15.950 --> 00:13:17.990
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Joe's got a license.
We could drive.</font>

180
00:13:18.019 --> 00:13:21.289
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The last time he took a trip,
he wrecked his dad's car.</font>

181
00:13:21.322 --> 00:13:23.192
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Whose car is he figuring
on wrecking this time?</font>

182
00:13:23.224 --> 00:13:24.424
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BOY ON TV: Yours.</font>

183
00:13:25.326 --> 00:13:26.356
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">He thought...</font>

184
00:13:26.394 --> 00:13:27.894
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I know what he thought.</font>

185
00:13:27.929 --> 00:13:31.199
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But I wouldn't trust
Joe Phillips
with a pogo stick.</font>

186
00:13:35.336 --> 00:13:37.706
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Please, Dad.
I'll be careful.</font>

187
00:13:37.738 --> 00:13:40.508
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">How can you be careful
if he's driving?</font>

188
00:13:40.541 --> 00:13:42.601
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You never let me
do anything.</font>

189
00:13:42.643 --> 00:13:44.513
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm not gonna
let you do this.</font>

190
00:13:44.545 --> 00:13:46.645
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You'd think
I was a juvenile
or something.</font>

191
00:13:46.680 --> 00:13:48.520
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">When you act this way,
you are.</font>

192
00:13:48.549 --> 00:13:49.959
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Now eat your dinner.</font>

193
00:13:49.984 --> 00:13:52.284
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm not hungry.</font>

194
00:13:52.320 --> 00:13:54.630
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then excuse yourself
and leave the table.</font>

195
00:14:09.637 --> 00:14:11.137
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(DOOR OPENING)</font>

196
00:14:18.412 --> 00:14:21.412
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mother, come on,
we'll be late for church.</font>

197
00:14:23.384 --> 00:14:25.914
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You all go on ahead
without me, honey.</font>

198
00:14:27.588 --> 00:14:29.888
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mama's having
one of her days.</font>

199
00:14:31.392 --> 00:14:32.852
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">All right.</font>

200
00:14:45.573 --> 00:14:51.343
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm reminded of the story
of the missionary doctor
and his wife</font>

201
00:14:51.379 --> 00:14:55.689
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">who were surprised
by bandits.</font>

202
00:14:55.716 --> 00:15:00.826
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You see, these thieves
were terrible men.</font>

203
00:15:00.854 --> 00:15:07.494
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Bloodthirsty. Vicious.
They not only
robbed their victims,</font>

204
00:15:07.528 --> 00:15:12.438
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">they slit their throats
and laughed
as they watched them die.</font>

205
00:15:12.466 --> 00:15:14.006
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You all don't hear me.</font>

206
00:15:14.035 --> 00:15:17.975
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">This poor doctor and his wife
ran for their lives</font>

207
00:15:18.006 --> 00:15:21.676
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">as the thieves chased them
across rocky, barren land.</font>

208
00:15:21.709 --> 00:15:25.319
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">These missionaries' feet
were cut open by sharp stones.</font>

209
00:15:25.346 --> 00:15:27.616
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Their clothes were
torn by brambles,</font>

210
00:15:27.648 --> 00:15:32.088
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and, finally,
they came upon
a great fortress,</font>

211
00:15:32.120 --> 00:15:34.990
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but the Bandit King
was right behind them.</font>

212
00:15:36.857 --> 00:15:41.267
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The doctor ran up to
the front door of the fortress
and tried to open it.</font>

213
00:15:41.295 --> 00:15:43.135
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But it was locked.</font>

214
00:15:43.164 --> 00:15:48.734
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If only someone would
let them in.
No one was there.</font>

215
00:15:48.769 --> 00:15:50.609
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And the doctor
and his wife hid,</font>

216
00:15:50.638 --> 00:15:54.648
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but the Bandit King saw them
and drew his sword.</font>

217
00:15:54.675 --> 00:15:58.675
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">There appeared to be
nothing that could
save God's good people.</font>

218
00:15:58.712 --> 00:15:59.842
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(SQUEAKING)</font>

219
00:15:59.880 --> 00:16:01.090
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(HORSE NEIGHING)</font>

220
00:16:07.988 --> 00:16:10.698
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The Bandit King was after me,
and so I hid under some straw,</font>

221
00:16:10.724 --> 00:16:13.094
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and a blue mouse came out
and scared his horse.</font>

222
00:16:13.127 --> 00:16:16.427
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And I got away.
I saw it in my brain.</font>

223
00:16:16.464 --> 00:16:20.164
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That's good.
That's your imagination
working.</font>

224
00:16:20.201 --> 00:16:22.361
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But it was real,
it was really real.</font>

225
00:16:22.403 --> 00:16:24.133
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Did I say it wasn't real?
It's not real.</font>

226
00:16:24.172 --> 00:16:25.332
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That's why it's called
imagination, dummy.</font>

227
00:16:25.373 --> 00:16:26.433
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Shut up.</font>

228
00:16:26.474 --> 00:16:29.074
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Watch your mouth, Curtis.</font>

229
00:16:29.110 --> 00:16:31.180
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mother, I want to
be a doctor.</font>

230
00:16:31.212 --> 00:16:34.512
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">A missionary doctor,
just like the one
Pastor Ford told us about.</font>

231
00:16:34.548 --> 00:16:37.958
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You can be anything
you want to be
in this life,</font>

232
00:16:37.985 --> 00:16:40.825
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">as long as you're
willing to work at it.</font>

233
00:16:40.854 --> 00:16:42.754
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That goes for you,
too, Curtis.</font>

234
00:16:44.858 --> 00:16:46.928
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">God will not abandon you.</font>

235
00:16:52.433 --> 00:16:54.233
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CHURCH BELL TOLLING)</font>

236
00:16:59.073 --> 00:17:00.343
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Excuse me.</font>

237
00:17:04.412 --> 00:17:06.512
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I need to talk to someone.</font>

238
00:17:08.182 --> 00:17:10.752
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I have a darkness
I can't control.</font>

239
00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:17.160
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Come with me, ma'am.
Let's see if we can help you.
All right?</font>

240
00:17:23.731 --> 00:17:27.131
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">SONYA:
I've spent my childhood
in foster care.</font>

241
00:17:27.168 --> 00:17:30.008
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">When my husband,
Mr. Carson,
married me,</font>

242
00:17:30.037 --> 00:17:32.577
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">he was my ticket
out of there.</font>

243
00:17:32.606 --> 00:17:34.606
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">How old were you?</font>

244
00:17:34.642 --> 00:17:35.742
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thirteen.</font>

245
00:17:37.311 --> 00:17:39.611
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We were happy.</font>

246
00:17:39.647 --> 00:17:42.687
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We had a lovely home,
two beautiful boys.</font>

247
00:17:45.919 --> 00:17:47.059
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then what?</font>

248
00:17:50.124 --> 00:17:51.524
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(BREATHING DEEPLY)</font>

249
00:17:52.393 --> 00:17:54.193
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't like to
talk about it.</font>

250
00:18:01.769 --> 00:18:04.739
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">He had another wife
and kids.</font>

251
00:18:09.277 --> 00:18:12.517
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">When I found out,
my life fell apart.</font>

252
00:18:12.546 --> 00:18:14.586
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">When was this, Mrs. Carson?</font>

253
00:18:18.986 --> 00:18:20.586
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Five years back.</font>

254
00:18:22.423 --> 00:18:23.893
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But I couldn't
leave my husband</font>

255
00:18:23.924 --> 00:18:25.694
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">'cause my boys
needed their daddy</font>

256
00:18:25.726 --> 00:18:29.226
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and I didn't know how
I'd make it on my own.</font>

257
00:18:29.263 --> 00:18:30.993
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Are you still together?</font>

258
00:18:31.031 --> 00:18:32.091
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No.</font>

259
00:18:33.467 --> 00:18:35.037
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I found out
he was dealing drugs,</font>

260
00:18:35.068 --> 00:18:37.038
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">so me and the boys
moved to Boston.</font>

261
00:18:37.070 --> 00:18:38.310
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I've got a sister there.</font>

262
00:18:38.339 --> 00:18:40.379
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Why'd you come back
to Detroit?</font>

263
00:18:40.408 --> 00:18:43.748
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I got the house
in the divorce,
and I kept it.</font>

264
00:18:43.777 --> 00:18:45.547
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I rent it out for income,</font>

265
00:18:47.047 --> 00:18:50.657
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but I've been saving money
in a cookie jar,</font>

266
00:18:50.684 --> 00:18:53.114
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and me and my boys
are gonna move back in.</font>

267
00:18:54.455 --> 00:18:55.985
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">How do you support yourself?</font>

268
00:18:56.023 --> 00:18:59.453
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I clean houses,
and I baby-sit.</font>

269
00:18:59.493 --> 00:19:01.023
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That's about
all I can do.</font>

270
00:19:06.734 --> 00:19:08.534
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Nobody knows this.</font>

271
00:19:14.908 --> 00:19:16.308
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm so dumb,</font>

272
00:19:17.311 --> 00:19:19.141
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I can't even read.</font>

273
00:19:24.151 --> 00:19:28.751
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And I fear my boys
are gonna turn out
the same way.</font>

274
00:19:29.990 --> 00:19:31.830
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And nothing's
gonna work out.</font>

275
00:19:34.595 --> 00:19:36.525
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I try to fight
these feelings.</font>

276
00:19:36.564 --> 00:19:38.894
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't show them
to Bennie and Curtis.</font>

277
00:19:40.601 --> 00:19:42.001
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But, lately,</font>

278
00:19:43.771 --> 00:19:45.431
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I can't stop them.</font>

279
00:19:50.611 --> 00:19:53.141
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I even think about
killing myself.</font>

280
00:19:55.816 --> 00:20:00.886
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Mrs. Carson,
what would you say to
checking yourself in with us?</font>

281
00:20:02.956 --> 00:20:04.026
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No.
Just for a little while.</font>

282
00:20:04.057 --> 00:20:06.097
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I can't afford
to do anything like...</font>

283
00:20:06.126 --> 00:20:08.566
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Don't think
about the money.</font>

284
00:20:09.497 --> 00:20:10.837
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We'll find the money.</font>

285
00:20:26.847 --> 00:20:30.287
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Boys, I'm gonna be
going away
for a little while.</font>

286
00:20:30.318 --> 00:20:32.188
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What?
What do you mean?</font>

287
00:20:32.219 --> 00:20:33.459
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Where?</font>

288
00:20:33.487 --> 00:20:34.787
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Just for a few weeks.</font>

289
00:20:34.822 --> 00:20:37.892
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm going back to Boston
to see your aunt Jean Avery.</font>

290
00:20:37.925 --> 00:20:39.995
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Can't we come with you?
No.</font>

291
00:20:40.027 --> 00:20:43.497
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You got school.
You got homework.</font>

292
00:20:43.531 --> 00:20:45.931
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">So, you're just gonna
leave us alone?</font>

293
00:20:45.966 --> 00:20:47.836
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Of course not.</font>

294
00:20:47.868 --> 00:20:50.378
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Sister Scott is gonna come
and stay with you.</font>

295
00:20:52.906 --> 00:20:59.146
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">In the meantime,
I want you boys
to do me a favor.</font>

296
00:20:59.179 --> 00:21:02.189
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I want you both to learn
your times tables
while I'm gone.</font>

297
00:21:02.215 --> 00:21:03.245
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">What?
No way!</font>

298
00:21:03.283 --> 00:21:04.853
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You can do it.</font>

299
00:21:04.885 --> 00:21:07.155
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Do you know
how many there are?</font>

300
00:21:07.187 --> 00:21:08.487
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">That could take a year.</font>

301
00:21:08.522 --> 00:21:10.652
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Won't take my boys a year.
You're smart.</font>

302
00:21:10.691 --> 00:21:13.051
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Not that smart.
Nobody can
memorize them.</font>

303
00:21:13.093 --> 00:21:15.723
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I did, and I just went
to the third grade.</font>

304
00:21:16.864 --> 00:21:18.264
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But it's hard work.</font>

305
00:21:18.298 --> 00:21:19.798
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Well,</font>

306
00:21:19.833 --> 00:21:22.403
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">hard work ain't
never hurt nobody.</font>

307
00:21:22.436 --> 00:21:24.976
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Besides, you ain't
going outside to play
till you learn them tables.</font>

308
00:21:25.005 --> 00:21:27.005
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Wait. Mother, please, no.
Come on, that's not fair.</font>

309
00:21:27.040 --> 00:21:30.420
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Come on, Mother.
You're the meanest mom
in the world.</font>

310
00:21:33.947 --> 00:21:35.717
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(MEN SINGING ON TV)</font>

311
00:21:38.952 --> 00:21:40.482
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CURTIS: Five times four.</font>

312
00:21:40.521 --> 00:21:41.621
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thirty.</font>

313
00:21:41.655 --> 00:21:43.125
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">No.</font>

314
00:21:43.156 --> 00:21:44.296
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thirty-one?</font>

315
00:21:44.324 --> 00:21:46.254
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">This isn't
a guessing game,
Bennie.</font>

316
00:21:46.293 --> 00:21:48.463
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Bennie, listen
to your brother.</font>

317
00:21:54.968 --> 00:21:56.408
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Here you are,
Mrs. Phillman.</font>

318
00:21:56.437 --> 00:21:58.007
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MRS. PHILLMAN:
Thank you.</font>

319
00:22:01.442 --> 00:22:03.342
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">NURSE: Mildred?
MILDRED: No.</font>

320
00:22:04.044 --> 00:22:05.974
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)</font>

321
00:22:41.114 --> 00:22:42.344
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MISS WILLIAMSON: Kathy?</font>

322
00:22:42.382 --> 00:22:43.682
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Twenty-two.</font>

323
00:22:45.052 --> 00:22:46.112
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MISS WILLIAMSON: Mark?</font>

324
00:22:46.153 --> 00:22:47.523
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Twenty-five
out of 25.</font>

325
00:22:47.555 --> 00:22:48.855
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Excellent.</font>

326
00:22:49.623 --> 00:22:51.523
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Benjamin?</font>

327
00:22:51.559 --> 00:22:53.629
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Benjamin?
I didn't cheat.</font>

328
00:22:53.661 --> 00:22:56.661
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I didn't say you did.
What's your score?</font>

329
00:22:57.898 --> 00:22:59.768
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Twenty-four out of 25.</font>

330
00:22:59.800 --> 00:23:01.610
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CHILDREN EXCLAIMING)</font>

331
00:23:02.836 --> 00:23:04.736
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN: Sister Scott!
Sister Scott!</font>

332
00:23:05.506 --> 00:23:06.576
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I got an A!</font>

333
00:23:06.607 --> 00:23:08.047
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I got an A.</font>

334
00:23:08.075 --> 00:23:09.905
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Sister Scott!
Sister Scott!</font>

335
00:23:13.547 --> 00:23:17.317
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I got... Mother!</font>

336
00:23:17.350 --> 00:23:18.520
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CHUCKLING)</font>

337
00:23:18.552 --> 00:23:21.882
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I missed you.
I missed you.</font>

