858
00:59:43.068 --> 00:59:44.138
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">with half a brain?</font>

859
00:59:44.169 --> 00:59:45.739
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's not as bad
as it sounds.</font>

860
00:59:46.537 --> 00:59:48.437
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We don't know why,</font>

861
00:59:48.473 --> 00:59:51.873
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but a child's brain
has a remarkable ability
to recover.</font>

862
00:59:51.910 --> 00:59:55.820
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's as if the brain cells
haven't decided what they want
to be when they grow up.</font>

863
00:59:55.847 --> 00:59:59.047
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">They take on the functions
of the diseased cells</font>

864
00:59:59.084 --> 01:00:01.954
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and then eventually
restore the
neurological function.</font>

865
01:00:01.987 --> 01:00:04.287
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You think
there's a chance
this will work?</font>

866
01:00:04.322 --> 01:00:06.392
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes. I do.</font>

867
01:00:07.859 --> 01:00:12.269
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But it is a gamble.
There's no way around that.</font>

868
01:00:12.297 --> 01:00:16.807
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If Cynthia survives,
she could be paralyzed
on her right side.</font>

869
01:00:16.835 --> 01:00:20.175
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The left side of the brain
controls the speech area.</font>

870
01:00:20.205 --> 01:00:23.745
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">She may lose
her ability to speak.</font>

871
01:00:23.775 --> 01:00:26.215
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Have you done
