01:14:09.700 --> 01:14:11.740
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Like a faucet
that's all dried up.</font>

1013
01:14:14.505 --> 01:14:17.745
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I felt that way
plenty of times.</font>

1014
01:14:17.775 --> 01:14:20.445
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The thing is,
you got to find out
what's blocking it</font>

1015
01:14:20.477 --> 01:14:22.777
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and move that thing
out the way.</font>

1016
01:14:22.813 --> 01:14:24.643
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't know
what's blocking it.</font>

1017
01:14:25.716 --> 01:14:27.116
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Sure you do.</font>

1018
01:14:31.656 --> 01:14:35.496
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You may not be able
to bring back your babies
by saving these,</font>

1019
01:14:37.061 --> 01:14:41.561
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">but, even if you fail,
at least you did something.</font>

1020
01:14:45.836 --> 01:14:47.076
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Bennie.</font>

1021
01:14:51.676 --> 01:14:54.916
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You can do this.
Sure you can.</font>

1022
01:14:58.148 --> 01:15:02.588
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You got
all the world in here.</font>

1023
01:15:04.321 --> 01:15:07.151
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You just gotta see beyond
what you can see.</font>

1024
01:15:10.227 --> 01:15:12.127
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes. Come on.</font>

1025
01:15:14.999 --> 01:15:15.999
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yeah.
Yeah.</font>

1026
01:16:12.156 --> 01:16:17.966
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">DR. ROGERS: Hello?
Mark, we're a go.</font>

1027
01:16:17.995 --> 01:16:21.135
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN: First off, we'll need
to have the room wired
with emergency power,</font>

1028
01:16:21.165 --> 01:16:23.035
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">in case there's
an electrical failure.</font>

1029
01:16:23.067 --> 01:16:24.467
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Then we'll need
two of everything,</font>

1030
01:16:24.501 --> 01:16:27.531
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">two anesthesia monitors,
two heart lung machines,</font>

1031
01:16:27.571 --> 01:16:31.141
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">enough people on each team
to cover both babies.</font>

1032
01:16:31.175 --> 01:16:35.215
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We'll need
an anesthesiology team,
a team of cardiac surgeons,</font>

1033
01:16:35.245 --> 01:16:38.745
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">a team of plastic surgeons,
a team of neurosurgeons.</font>

1034
01:16:38.783 --> 01:16:42.983
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">And we'll need to figure out
how to fit all 50 of us
into one operating room.</font>

1035
01:16:43.020 --> 01:16:46.360
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Each team must rehearse
their respective procedures
step-by-step,</font>

1036
01:16:46.390 --> 01:16:48.900
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and each team must
develop scenarios</font>

1037
01:16:48.926 --> 01:16:51.126
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">for the worst possible things
that could happen.</font>

1038
01:16:51.161 --> 01:16:54.961
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If one baby dies,
we need to separate him
as fast as possible</font>

1039
01:16:54.999 --> 01:16:58.039
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and give
all shared tissue
to the surviving twin.</font>

1040
01:16:58.068 --> 01:17:01.708
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Cardiothoracic will start
their procedures at 6:00 a.m.</font>

1041
01:17:02.907 --> 01:17:04.747
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(REPORTERS CLAMORING)</font>

1042
01:17:10.114 --> 01:17:14.414
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Hello, again, Peter, Augusta.
Welcome to Johns Hopkins.</font>

1043
01:17:16.286 --> 01:17:18.756
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Your sons' blood vessels
are like tiny faucets</font>

1044
01:17:18.789 --> 01:17:21.599
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">with only so much blood
to lose.</font>

1045
01:17:21.625 --> 01:17:23.865
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Now, if we can
turn off the faucets,</font>

1046
01:17:23.894 --> 01:17:26.064
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">we can keep your sons
from bleeding.</font>

1047
01:17:27.798 --> 01:17:30.168
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The only way to do this
is to stop their hearts.</font>

1048
01:17:30.200 --> 01:17:31.410
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Stop their...</font>

1049
01:17:31.435 --> 01:17:33.135
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN: It's not
a new procedure.</font>

1050
01:17:33.170 --> 01:17:36.080
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's been used
by cardiovascular surgeons
for years.</font>

1051
01:17:36.106 --> 01:17:39.376
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's just never been applied
in a situation like this.</font>

1052
01:17:39.409 --> 01:17:43.719
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Now, we can do it
in infants for an hour
without causing brain damage.</font>

1053
01:17:43.748 --> 01:17:45.448
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">But that hour
is critical.</font>

1054
01:17:45.482 --> 01:17:47.182
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Why?
What happens
in that hour?</font>

1055
01:17:47.217 --> 01:17:49.087
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We'll stop their hearts,</font>

1056
01:17:49.119 --> 01:17:52.159
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">then spend that hour
reconstructing
all the blood vessels</font>

1057
01:17:52.189 --> 01:17:54.829
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">so that when
their hearts start again,</font>

1058
01:17:54.859 --> 01:17:57.329
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">there won't be
any life-threatening
loss of blood.</font>

1059
01:17:58.528 --> 01:18:00.698
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">All in one hour?</font>

1060
01:18:00.731 --> 01:18:03.491
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Which is why
we've rehearsed
and rehearsed,</font>

1061
01:18:04.668 --> 01:18:06.938
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">and why we need to pray.</font>

1062
01:18:06.971 --> 01:18:08.801
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You pray, Doctor?</font>

1063
01:18:08.839 --> 01:18:09.909
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Every day.</font>

1064
01:18:14.378 --> 01:18:17.218
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

1065
01:18:17.247 --> 01:18:19.487
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(MACHINES BEEPING
RHYTHMICALLY)</font>

1066
01:18:26.490 --> 01:18:28.600
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CARDIOTHORACIC SURGEON:
I'm removing the pericardium</font>

1067
01:18:28.625 --> 01:18:31.225
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">to be used later
as vascular tissue.</font>

1068
01:18:46.343 --> 01:18:49.773
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Cardio is done.
All yours, Ben.</font>

1069
01:19:00.090 --> 01:19:01.730
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">My light, please.</font>

1070
01:19:12.903 --> 01:19:14.133
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Scalpel.</font>

1071
01:19:22.279 --> 01:19:24.189
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)</font>

1072
01:19:36.961 --> 01:19:41.591
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I've opened the dura
and revealed the venous sinus
that they share.</font>

1073
01:19:41.631 --> 01:19:45.461
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm going to
start separation now,
starting below the torcula.</font>

1074
01:19:53.878 --> 01:19:55.448
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">There's a lot
of bleeding.</font>

1075
01:19:58.515 --> 01:20:00.815
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Close it up.
We'll try a different area.</font>

1076
01:20:03.854 --> 01:20:05.754
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">FEMALE NURSE:
Vital signs are stable.</font>

1077
01:20:12.429 --> 01:20:16.569
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Lord, it's like
a lake of blood,
it's huge.</font>

1078
01:20:19.603 --> 01:20:20.803
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Stitch.</font>

1079
01:20:26.310 --> 01:20:28.450
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We have to
start hypothermic arrest.</font>

1080
01:20:28.478 --> 01:20:30.318
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MALE DOCTOR: Ben, we can't
stop the hearts right now.</font>

1081
01:20:30.347 --> 01:20:32.547
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">We haven't finished
separating all the veins.</font>

1082
01:20:32.582 --> 01:20:34.712
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If we do it now,
it'll cut too deeply
into our hour.</font>

1083
01:20:34.751 --> 01:20:37.251
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">If we don't
stop the hearts,
they'll bleed out.</font>

1084
01:20:37.287 --> 01:20:39.487
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Start cooling the blood.</font>

1085
01:20:39.523 --> 01:20:40.583
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Cooling.</font>

1086
01:20:43.560 --> 01:20:45.930
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CARDIOTHORACIC SURGEON:
Prepare to inject
the saline coolant solution</font>

1087
01:20:45.963 --> 01:20:47.363
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">to replace the blood.</font>

1088
01:20:54.204 --> 01:20:55.934
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Aortic cross-clamp.</font>

1089
01:21:01.811 --> 01:21:03.571
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Cardioplegic needle.</font>

1090
01:21:06.050 --> 01:21:08.920
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">FEMALE NURSE:
Blood cooling
to 20 degrees.</font>

1091
01:21:11.588 --> 01:21:14.528
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">The hearts are stopped.
Turn off
the heart-lung machine.</font>

1092
01:21:14.558 --> 01:21:17.268
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Okay. We have one hour
to finish separation,</font>

1093
01:21:17.294 --> 01:21:20.194
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">rebuild the severed veins
and reconstruct the torcula.</font>

1094
01:21:21.231 --> 01:21:22.461
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Pick up.</font>

1095
01:21:24.701 --> 01:21:25.961
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Bipolar.</font>

1096
01:21:26.003 --> 01:21:27.333
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">More suction, please.</font>

1097
01:21:34.878 --> 01:21:36.648
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">WOMAN ON PA: Dr. Wong,
call the page operator.</font>

1098
01:21:39.816 --> 01:21:42.656
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN: I'm now separating
the sagittal sinus.</font>

1099
01:21:47.224 --> 01:21:49.594
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Okay.
Prepare for separation.</font>

1100
01:21:49.626 --> 01:21:50.626
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MALE DOCTOR: Right.</font>

1101
01:21:54.531 --> 01:21:56.231
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Set.</font>

1102
01:21:56.266 --> 01:21:57.606
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I'm ready to go.</font>

1103
01:21:58.735 --> 01:22:00.465
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">All right, on my mark.</font>

1104
01:22:01.638 --> 01:22:06.978
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Three, two, one,
separate.</font>

1105
01:22:07.011 --> 01:22:08.971
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN: Slowly.
MALE DOCTOR: Easy.</font>

1106
01:22:11.581 --> 01:22:12.881
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN:
Get ready with the drapes.</font>

1107
01:22:12.916 --> 01:22:14.916
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Make sure we don't
contaminate the field.</font>

1108
01:22:18.455 --> 01:22:20.155
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">FEMALE NURSE:
Get that drape, too.</font>

1109
01:22:20.190 --> 01:22:21.230
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MALE DOCTOR:
Go ahead, hang it.</font>

1110
01:22:21.258 --> 01:22:22.358
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Adjust that light, please.</font>

1111
01:22:22.392 --> 01:22:23.852
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">FEMALE NURSE:
I got the drapes.</font>

1112
01:22:23.893 --> 01:22:25.793
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)</font>

1113
01:22:28.265 --> 01:22:29.495
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MALE DOCTOR:
You adjust the drape?</font>

1114
01:22:31.635 --> 01:22:33.535
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">BEN: Anesthesia?
How does it look?</font>

1115
01:22:33.570 --> 01:22:35.040
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">ANESTHESIOLOGIST: Give us
a few minutes, Ben.</font>

1116
01:22:41.811 --> 01:22:44.511
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Start the restructuring
of the torcula.</font>

1117
01:22:54.924 --> 01:22:57.964
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">This is taking three times
as long as I thought.</font>

1118
01:22:59.163 --> 01:23:01.133
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">It's just too darn small.</font>

1119
01:23:02.666 --> 01:23:04.306
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">ANESTHESIOLOGIST:
Pressure's coming down, Ben.</font>

1120
01:23:14.744 --> 01:23:17.184
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">DR. LONG: Done with
vascular reconstruction.</font>

1121
01:23:17.214 --> 01:23:18.544
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Turn on the pump.
Yes, Doctor.</font>

1122
01:23:18.582 --> 01:23:19.642
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">DR. LONG:
Start re-warming the blood.</font>

1123
01:23:19.683 --> 01:23:21.883
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes, Doctor.
Warming the blood.</font>

1124
01:23:28.858 --> 01:23:30.898
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">I don't think
I can do it in time.</font>

1125
01:23:34.098 --> 01:23:36.268
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">FEMALE NURSE: One minute,
30 seconds, Doctor.</font>

1126
01:23:54.618 --> 01:23:56.588
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">SONYA: You don't
need the book.</font>

1127
01:23:56.620 --> 01:23:59.930
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">You got the book
inside you.</font>

1128
01:24:13.137 --> 01:24:14.237
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Done.</font>

1129
01:24:15.639 --> 01:24:19.279
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Start the pumps.
Warm the blood.</font>

1130
01:24:19.309 --> 01:24:21.049
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CARDIOTHORACIC SURGEON:
Starting the pumps.</font>

1131
01:24:25.982 --> 01:24:28.412
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Get ready to
start the heart, baby one.</font>

1132
01:24:31.087 --> 01:24:32.887
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CARDIOTHORACIC SURGEON 1:
Paddles in, baby two.</font>

1133
01:24:33.890 --> 01:24:35.260
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(POWER CHARGING UP)</font>

1134
01:24:35.292 --> 01:24:36.522
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CARDIOTHORACIC SURGEON:
Clear, baby one.</font>

1135
01:24:36.560 --> 01:24:38.630
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Okay. Do it.</font>

1136
01:24:38.662 --> 01:24:39.762
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(BEEPING)</font>

1137
01:24:41.631 --> 01:24:44.161
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Baby two.
Charge to 10.</font>

1138
01:24:45.202 --> 01:24:47.372
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(POWER CHARGING UP)</font>

1139
01:24:47.404 --> 01:24:50.034
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Clear. All right, do it.</font>

1140
01:24:50.073 --> 01:24:51.173
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(BEEPING)</font>

1141
01:24:55.545 --> 01:24:57.215
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(MONITORS BEEPING)</font>

1142
01:24:58.014 --> 01:24:59.584
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Looks like sinus rhythm.</font>

1143
01:25:10.126 --> 01:25:12.396
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Start closing up
the chest.</font>

1144
01:25:12.429 --> 01:25:14.569
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">CARDIOTHORACIC SURGEON:
Closing.</font>

1145
01:25:14.598 --> 01:25:17.968
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Begin closing the dura,
Dr. Long.</font>

1146
01:25:19.703 --> 01:25:20.803
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Closing, Ben.</font>

1147
01:25:22.339 --> 01:25:23.509
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Stitch, please.</font>

1148
01:25:26.210 --> 01:25:27.480
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Stitch, please.</font>

1149
01:25:29.813 --> 01:25:32.113
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Someone let the parents know
we're almost finished.</font>

1150
01:25:32.148 --> 01:25:33.548
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Yes, Doctor.</font>

1151
01:25:34.851 --> 01:25:37.781
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Close them up. Dr. Long?</font>

1152
01:25:37.821 --> 01:25:40.051
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">One more stitch, Ben.</font>

1153
01:25:40.089 --> 01:25:41.799
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Disconnect my light, please.</font>

1154
01:25:43.760 --> 01:25:45.030
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Light, please.</font>

1155
01:25:47.264 --> 01:25:51.334
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Neuro's clear.
Plastic surgeons,
prepare to begin.</font>

1156
01:25:51.368 --> 01:25:53.668
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thank you, Ben.
Plastics, stepping in.</font>

1157
01:26:26.603 --> 01:26:28.573
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">WOMAN ON PA:
Ultrasound tech
to Labor 4, please.</font>

1158
01:26:28.605 --> 01:26:29.775
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Peter.</font>

1159
01:26:34.043 --> 01:26:35.243
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Doctor?</font>

1160
01:26:36.880 --> 01:26:39.450
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Which child would you
like to see first?</font>

1161
01:26:39.483 --> 01:26:40.543
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(GASPING)</font>

1162
01:26:40.584 --> 01:26:41.684
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(SPEAKING GERMAN)</font>

1163
01:26:41.718 --> 01:26:44.218
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Thank you. Thank you.</font>

1164
01:26:45.255 --> 01:26:46.585
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(CRYING)
Thank you.</font>

1165
01:26:52.396 --> 01:26:53.526
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(SOBBING)</font>

1166
01:26:59.669 --> 01:27:01.679
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Good.
Yeah.</font>

1167
01:27:01.705 --> 01:27:03.735
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">PETER: I'm okay.</font>

1168
01:27:03.773 --> 01:27:04.803
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">PETER: Okay.
AUGUSTA: Yeah?</font>

1169
01:27:04.841 --> 01:27:06.841
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">PETER: Okay.</font>

1170
01:27:06.876 --> 01:27:08.716
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN: All right.
MAN 1: Congratulations.</font>

1171
01:27:08.745 --> 01:27:10.415
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN 2: Fantastic. Nice work.</font>

1172
01:27:13.983 --> 01:27:14.983
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">MAN: Good job.</font>

1173
01:27:16.620 --> 01:27:19.230
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">Ben, congratulations.
Incredible job.</font>

1174
01:27:40.644 --> 01:27:41.914
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(BABY GURGLING)</font>

1175
01:27:47.884 --> 01:27:49.084
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(BABY GURGLES)</font>

1176
01:28:19.749 --> 01:28:21.019
<font face="sans-serif" size="71">(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)</font>

1177
01:28:25.355 --> 01:28:27.225
